headline.main: DAMAGE IN EGYPT CLAIMED BY ITALY; Fascist Air Report Lists the French Warship Lorraine as 'Partially Destroyed' CAIRO PROTESTS TO ROME Note Denouncing the Killing of Civilians Coincides With Pressure to Enter War

lead_paragraph: ROME, Dec. 2 (UP)--The official Stefani news agency said today that Italian air attacks against the British on the Egyptian coast last month had damaged two warships, set two steamships afire, killed 200 soldiers and port workers and damaged airdromes.
